cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with Named Entity Recognition (NER) task on social media text, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and hence, is likely to be categorized under cs.CL.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper proposes a joint representation of text and image for NER task, which involves using computer vision techniques to process the image. Hence, it is likely to be categorized under cs.CV.
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with multimodal NER task, which involves processing both text and image. Hence, it is likely to be categorized under cs.MM.
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with text processing and information extraction, which are key components of information retrieval systems. Hence, it is likely to be categorized under cs.IR.
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes an end-to-end model for joint text and image representation, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG.
